<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 4:40PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN
ALLEGHANY...SOUTHWESTERN ROCKBRIDGE AND NORTHWESTERN BOTETOURT
COUNTIES IN WEST CENTRAL VIRGINIA THROUGH 515 PM EDT...
At 440 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gala, or near Eagle Rock, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clifton Forge...
Eagle Rock...
Iron Gate...
Glen Wilton...
Longdale Furnace...
and Gala.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
